    "protocolName": "Tether Gold (XAUT)",
    "protocolSlug": "Tether-Gold",
    "chain": "Ethereum",
    "projectType": "stablecoin",
    "tokenName": "XAUT",
    "description": "Tether Gold (XAUt) is an ERC-20 token issued by TG Commodities Limited where each unit represents one troy ounce of physical gold held in custody, with a current circulating market value of $3.23B. The token is deployed behind an EIP-1967 transparent proxy and exposes off-chain controlled administrative functions: a single owner can mint new supply, freeze and destroy balances on a blocklist, and an upgrade authority can replace the implementation contract at any time. Both the token's `owner` and the proxy's upgrade authority resolve to the same custom 3-of-6 MultiSigWallet, making the multisig the single point of trust for supply, censorship, and code changes. There is no on-chain timelock or upgrade delay — once three signers confirm a transaction it executes immediately. This review covers only the Ethereum-native XAUt contract; XAUT0, the cross-chain version available on other networks, is a separate offering issued by Everdawn Labs via LayerZero and is out of scope here."
  },
